race.comment: ARE YOU KIDDING (3) firmed to start at $2.70 but found the winner a shade too good on debut last start over 1000m at Muswellbrook. Has a terrible gate to contend with but if things go right he looks a great chance to open the account. ZO FRILLING (8) is the danger first-up from a 21-week spell. Raced well last prep but it should be noted at was all on soft or heavy tracks. Recent Tamworth trial winner who is a serious threat if she can bring the wet track form to a firmer surface. SILENT SERENADE (12) made it four minor placings from as many career runs when she found the line well but still finished 2.5 lengths behind ARE YOU KIDDING at Muswellbrook recently. Draws a far better gate today and can close that gap. HE'STHECHIEF (1) returns after a 195-day spell. Yet to be tried on a dry surface but his form with the sting out of the ground reads well. Keep him in mind. SCATPAK (2) hasn't been far away in his two runs this time in work and a slightly longer trip today helps.
